36:28.486 --> 36:28.986
THRILLER "PACIFIC HEIGHTS."

36:29.053 --> 36:30.855
NOT A LOT OF TYPECASTING
HERE.

36:30.922 --> 36:32.323
ACCIDENT OR DESIGN?

36:32.390 --> 36:34.625
>> Keaton: I WANTED TO SET IT UP
SO THAT I HAD MORE SHOTS.

36:34.692 --> 36:37.662
I WANTED TO BE ABLE TO PLAY
A
LOT OF DIFFERENT THINGS.

36:37.728 --> 36:40.264
BECAUSE, I LEARNED REAL QUICKLY
THAT THEY WERE GOING, "OH, WE

36:40.331 --> 36:40.798
LIKE WHEN HE DOES THAT.

36:40.865 --> 36:41.232
GET HIM TO DO THAT.

36:41.299 --> 36:44.602
LET'S HIRE HIM TO DO THAT
THING."

36:44.669 --> 36:46.604
I THOUGHT, "OH BOY, THAT COULD,
I THINK, FRANKLY, I WOULD HAVE

36:46.671 --> 36:47.872
BEEN OUT OF THE BUSINESS."

36:47.939 --> 36:52.610
PEOPLE WOULD HAVE BEEN, IF
THEY'RE NOT BORED ALREADY, BORED

36:52.677 --> 36:53.210
TO TEARS EARLY WITH ME.

36:53.277 --> 36:57.648
>> Wertheim: THIS OVERLAY OF
LIGHT AND DARK CONVINCED

36:57.715 --> 37:01.185
DIRECTOR TIM BURTON THAT MICHAEL
KEATON WAS RIGHT FOR THE LEAD IN

37:01.252 --> 37:04.689
HIS NEXT BIG BUDGET MOVIE:
"BATMAN."

37:04.755 --> 37:09.293
KEATON WOULD EMBODY BRUCE WAYNE
AS A COMPLICATED, EVEN TORMENTED

37:09.360 --> 37:10.695
TYCOON, HELL-BENT ON
JUSTICE.

37:10.761 --> 37:14.465
HARDCORE FANS OF THE DC
COMIC
HERO WERE HORRIFIED ABOUT

37:14.532 --> 37:16.667
CASTING MR. MOM AS THE CAPED
CRUSADER.

37:16.734 --> 37:20.171
>> Man: WHAT ARE YOU?

37:20.237 --> 37:21.272
>> Keaton: I'M BATMAN.

37:21.339 --> 37:22.673
YOU KNOW, I HAVE A LONG MEMORY.

37:22.740 --> 37:25.810
YOU KNOW, SO A COUPLE OCCASIONS
WHERE, YOU KNOW, PEOPLE WERE

37:25.876 --> 37:29.313
KIND OF-- NOT JUST, MAYBE
DID
MORE THAN DOUBT YOU.

37:29.380 --> 37:31.749
YOU GO, "OKAY, I'LL WAIT."

37:31.816 --> 37:33.618
>> Wertheim: PEERS, OR
REVIEWERS, OR?

37:33.684 --> 37:36.220
>> Keaton: JUST THINGS THAT
HAPPENED A COUPLE TIMES.

37:36.287 --> 37:36.854
YOU JUST KIND OF CLOCK IT.

37:36.921 --> 37:38.656
>> Wertheim: YOU REMEMBER
THAT
STUFF.

37:38.723 --> 37:39.690
>> Keaton: YEAH.

37:39.757 --> 37:41.292
>> Wertheim: SO YOU'RE
COMING
INTO THIS ROLE, AND YOU'RE
THE

37:41.359 --> 37:43.794
NEW BATMAN.

37:43.861 --> 37:45.262
>> Keaton: YEAH, YEAH.

37:45.329 --> 37:46.197
NO, I AM THE-- BATMAN.

37:46.263 --> 37:46.831
>> Wertheim: YOU'RE THE BATMAN.

37:46.897 --> 37:47.465
BUT YOU'VE GOT THIS
LINEAGE...

37:47.531 --> 37:48.833
>> Keaton: YEAH.

37:48.899 --> 37:49.367
LET'S BE CLEAR ABOUT THAT.

37:49.433 --> 37:51.402
NO, I'M KIDDING.

37:51.469 --> 37:54.872
(<i> LAUGHS </i>)
BATMAN, THE FIRST BATMAN, I

37:54.939 --> 37:57.274
THINK TIM AND I BOTH KNEW IF
THAT DOESN'T WORK, THAT ONE,
I

37:57.341 --> 37:58.743
HAD AWARENESS OF.

37:58.809 --> 38:00.378
I THOUGHT, "OOH, THIS-- THIS
COULD REALLY FAIL."

38:00.444 --> 38:02.279
(<i> LAUGHS </i>)
>> Wertheim: YEAH, I MEAN,
IT

38:02.346 --> 38:03.881
STRIKES ME, THAT'S ANOTHER RISK
OF A DIFFERENT KIND, RIGHT?

38:03.948 --> 38:04.749
>> Keaton: YEAH.

38:04.815 --> 38:05.349
YEAH.

38:05.416 --> 38:08.419
THERE WAS A LOT OF PRESSURE
ON
THAT MOVIE FOR EVERYBODY.

38:08.486 --> 38:13.357
>> Wertheim: HOLY
GAMBLE-THAT-
PAID-OFF, BATMAN.

38:13.424 --> 38:16.761
THE MOVIE MADE MORE THAN $400
MILLION AND CATAPULTED KEATON TO

38:16.827 --> 38:19.797
A NEW PLANE OF STARDOM--
PROOF
THAT RESISTING CONVENTIONAL

38:19.864 --> 38:21.565
HOLLYWOOD WISDOM HAD ITS
ADVANTAGES.

38:21.632 --> 38:26.704
KEATON CONTINUED HIS GAME OF
CHARACTER HOPSCOTCH IN
ANOTHER

38:26.771 --> 38:28.806
30 MOVIES, FROM SHAKESPEARE
TO
"SPOTLIGHT."

38:28.873 --> 38:33.344
SOME BROUGHT MORE BOX OFFICE
SUCCESS THAN OTHERS.

38:33.411 --> 38:37.014
BUT WHEN HE WASN'T ACTING,
KEATON WAS A HANDS-ON DAD TO HIS

38:37.081 --> 38:39.383
SON SEAN, WHO IS NOW 38 AND
A
SUCCESSFUL SONGWRITER IN LOS

38:39.450 --> 38:40.351
ANGELES.

38:40.418 --> 38:45.356
AND KEATON HAD REACHED A
POINT
WHERE HE COULD BE CHOOSY.

38:45.423 --> 38:50.895
IN 2014, ENTER "BIRDMAN,"
AND
KEATON'S ALMOST ABSURDIST
ROLE

38:50.961 --> 38:52.563
THAT EARNED HIM A GOLDEN
GLOBE
FOR BEST ACTOR.

38:52.630 --> 38:53.064
HARDEST ROLE YOU'VE HAD?

38:53.130 --> 38:54.532
>> Keaton: MOSTLY, YEAH.

38:54.598 --> 38:57.568
IT HAD TO BE SO SPECIFIC, AND SO
PRECISE.

38:57.635 --> 39:00.871
YOU ACTUALLY HAD TO BE, LIKE, ON
A CERTAIN WORD, OR A POINT IN

39:00.938 --> 39:04.809
THE SENTENCE, AND GEOGRAPHICALLY
IN A SPOT.

39:04.875 --> 39:09.280
LIKE, ON-- IN A HALLWAY OR DOWN
A SET OF STAIRS.

39:09.346 --> 39:09.814
SPECIFICALLY WORD PERFECT.

39:09.880 --> 39:10.815
AND IT WAS REALLY HARD.

39:10.881 --> 39:13.417
SCARY EVERY DAY.

39:13.484 --> 39:15.753
>> Wertheim: DO PEOPLE IN
YOUR
LINE OF WORK HAVE RIVALS,
LIKE

39:15.820 --> 39:16.754
ATHLETES?

39:16.821 --> 39:17.955
I MEAN, ARE YOU, YOU KNOW, "HEY,
BILL MURRAY, I'M COMING FOR

39:18.022 --> 39:19.256
YOU"?

39:19.323 --> 39:20.291
>> Keaton: I DON'T KNOW.

39:20.357 --> 39:21.425
YOU KNOW, THAT'S THE THING.

39:21.492 --> 39:22.827
THERE'S NOTHING WE CAN DO.

39:22.893 --> 39:24.995
YOU KNOW, WE CAN'T GO, LIKE, BOX
EACH OTHER.

39:25.062 --> 39:26.997
(<i> LAUGHS </i>)
YOU KNOW, I MEAN.

39:27.064 --> 39:28.799
WE'RE ALL IN A BROTHER AND
SISTERHOOD TO SOME DEGREE,
YOU

39:28.866 --> 39:29.467
KNOW?

39:29.533 --> 39:33.270
LIKE, YOU KNOW, THE CRITICISM OF
PEOPLE'S PERFORMANCES I FIND

39:33.337 --> 39:33.871
REALLY BUSH LEAGUE, YOU
KNOW?

39:33.938 --> 39:37.374
IT'S LIKE, "WHAT DO I KNOW?" I'M
NOT SURE I EVEN KNOW ENOUGH.

39:37.441 --> 39:37.908
AND I'M NOT BEING HUMBLE.

39:37.975 --> 39:40.578
I'M BEING HONEST.

39:40.644 --> 39:41.812
I DON'T-- I DON'T KNOW THAT I
EVEN KNOW ENOUGH TO SAY, "WELL,

39:41.879 --> 39:44.849
THAT'S NOT ANY GOOD."

39:44.915 --> 39:46.817
>> Wertheim: IN HIS LATEST
PROJECT, KEATON IS BACK TO

39:46.884 --> 39:49.420
INTERPRETING THE AMERICAN MALE.

39:49.487 --> 39:52.823
"DOPESICK," OUT THIS MONTH, IS A
HULU MINI-SERIES ABOUT THE

39:52.890 --> 39:54.492
COUNTRY'S OPIOID EPIDEMIC.

39:54.558 --> 39:56.727
>> Keaton: I WOULD NEVER
PRESCRIBE A NARCOTIC FOR

39:56.794 --> 39:57.394
MODERATE PAIN.

39:57.461 --> 40:01.398
>> Wertheim: KEATON PLAYS A
DOCTOR IN A COAL-MINING TOWN

40:01.465 --> 40:03.100
OVERWHELMED BY OXYCONTIN.

40:03.167 --> 40:05.402
BUT THIS TIME, HE ADMITS THERE'S
A LITTLE MORE TO THE PART.

40:05.469 --> 40:09.940
>> Keaton: YOU KNOW, THAT MEANS
A LOT TO ME, BECAUSE, YOU KNOW,

40:10.007 --> 40:13.177
I LOST A NEPHEW TO FENTANYL AND
HEROIN.

40:13.244 --> 40:16.180
>> Wertheim: WHAT'S IT LIKE WHEN
YOU HAVE THIS KIND OF PERSONAL

40:16.247 --> 40:16.814
CONNECTION TO A ROLE?

40:16.881 --> 40:21.418
>> Keaton: YOU HAVE TO
REMOVE
THE EMOTION AND JUST, LIKE I

40:21.485 --> 40:25.422
KEEP SAYING, YOU KNOW, WHAT'S--
WHAT'S THE JOB AT HAND, YOU

40:25.489 --> 40:28.826
KNOW, WHAT'S-- I'M JUST A
STORYTELLER.

40:28.893 --> 40:32.630
>> Wertheim: BEFITTING A MAN WHO
PIVOTS FROM ROLE TO ROLE, KEATON

40:32.696 --> 40:33.964
IS ESPECIALLY THRILLED BY
PITTSBURGH'S TRANSITION FROM

40:34.031 --> 40:36.767
STEEL TO TECH.

40:36.834 --> 40:40.471
HE RETURNS HOME OFTEN, AND
INVITED US TO A MODIFIED
STEEL

40:40.538 --> 40:44.942
MILL-TURNED-INNOVATION
CENTER
NOT FAR FROM WHERE HE GREW
UP.

40:45.009 --> 40:48.512
KEATON IS AN INVESTOR IN A
CONSTRUCTION COMPANY, NEXII,

40:48.579 --> 40:51.315
THAT HERE IN PITTSBURGH PLANS TO
MAKE ECO-FRIENDLY ALTERNATIVES

40:51.382 --> 40:52.817
TO CONCRETE.

40:52.883 --> 40:53.417
>> Keaton: I GET THIS.

40:53.484 --> 40:57.421
AND I ACTUALLY LIKE IT.

40:57.488 --> 41:01.225
AND IF I'M GOING TO-- MAN, JUST
LOOK AT THIS SUMMER.

41:01.292 --> 41:04.895
IF I'M GOING TO HAVE AN
OPPORTUNITY TO DO ANYTHING
AND

41:04.962 --> 41:07.631
PUT MY MONEY WHERE MY MOUTH IS,
YOU CAN'T JUST HAVE AN OPINION

41:07.698 --> 41:08.399
ABOUT CLIMATE CHANGE
ANYMORE.

41:08.465 --> 41:08.999
IT'S, LIKE, HERE, NOW.

41:09.066 --> 41:10.701
>> Wertheim: THE BILL'S COME
DUE, HUH?

41:10.768 --> 41:11.202
>> Keaton: THAT'S RIGHT.

41:11.268 --> 41:13.470
THE BILL'S-- THE BILL'S COME
DUE.

41:13.537 --> 41:16.407
>> Wertheim: KEATON WOULD
HAPPILY SPEND MORE TIME
HERE--

41:16.473 --> 41:20.477
AND IN MONTANA-- IF IT
WEREN'T
FOR THAT PESKY DAY JOB.

41:20.544 --> 41:22.580
HE JUST FINISHED FILMING
"THE
FLASH," REPRISING HIS ROLE
AS

41:22.646 --> 41:25.482
BATMAN, 30 YEARS AFTER HE
LEFT
THE FRANCHISE.

41:25.549 --> 41:28.886
AND WE HAD TO KNOW-- BUT, IS
THIS BRUCE WAYNE STILL THE

41:28.953 --> 41:33.490
TORTURED, SOMEWHAT DARK
FIGURE
HE WAS, AS WE RECALL?

41:33.557 --> 41:34.892
>> Keaton: ISH.

41:34.959 --> 41:40.865
HE'S KIND OF-- YOU KNOW, I CAN'T
GIVE TOO MUCH OF THIS AWAY.

41:40.931 --> 41:42.800
I'M ONE OF THOSE GUYS WHO GOES,
"WELL, I-- I-- I'M NOT GIVING

41:42.867 --> 41:43.767
THAT (<i> BLEEP </i>) AWAY."

41:43.834 --> 41:44.635
GO SEE THE MOVIE.

41:44.702 --> 41:46.871
>> Wertheim: HOW'S THE
COSTUME
FIT?

41:46.937 --> 41:49.473
>> Keaton: PROUD TO SAY, I
SLIPPED RIGHT BACK INTO IT.

41:49.540 --> 41:52.509
>> Wertheim: YOU'RE 70 YEARS
OLD, AND YOU'RE STILL
KICKING

41:52.576 --> 41:52.877
BAD GUYS' ASS.

41:52.943 --> 41:55.045
THAT'S GOT TO FEEL GOOD.

41:55.112 --> 41:56.080
>> Keaton: YEAH.

41:56.146 --> 41:57.481
IF YOU KNOW ANYBODY WHOSE
ASS
NEEDS KICKED, JUST DON'T
CALL

41:57.548 --> 41:58.549
ME.

41:58.616 --> 42:03.320
(<i> LAUGHS </i>)
(<i> TICKING </i>)

42:07.591 --> 42:09.760
>> Whitaker: WITH THE DEATH
OF
GENERAL COLIN POWELL THIS
PAST

42:09.827 --> 42:13.764
WEEK, AMERICA LOST ONE MORE
OF
ITS DWINDLING SUPPLY OF WISE

42:13.831 --> 42:17.468
MEN, AND WISE WOMEN-- WASHINGTON
HANDS WITH SEASONED PERSPECTIVE

42:17.534 --> 42:21.405
WHO COULD TELL A PRESIDENT WHEN
HE IS WRONG.

42:21.472 --> 42:23.173
LIKE GENERAL POWELL, THEY
WEREN'T ALWAYS RIGHT, BUT COULD

42:23.240 --> 42:28.112
BE TRUSTED TO HOLD THE NATION'S
INTEREST ABOVE PERSONAL

42:28.178 --> 42:29.179
AMBITION.

42:29.246 --> 42:32.650
SAM NUNN, OLYMPIA SNOWE, AND
GEORGE MITCHELL CAME FROM
THE

42:32.716 --> 42:33.417
SENATE.

42:33.484 --> 42:37.755
JIM BAKER WAS AN
ESTABLISHMENT
LAWYER.

42:37.821 --> 42:40.724
A FEW WERE FROM WALL STREET, OR,
LIKE GENERAL POWELL, FROM THE

42:40.791 --> 42:41.158
MILITARY.

42:41.225 --> 42:45.763
LAST SUNDAY ON THIS
BROADCAST,
WE HEARD FROM ANOTHER,
ROBERT

42:45.829 --> 42:47.331
GATES, WHO ROSE THROUGH THE
NATIONAL SECURITY AND

42:47.398 --> 42:49.767
INTELLIGENCE COMMUNITIES.

42:49.833 --> 42:53.170
MOST OF THEM ARE NOW RETIRED OR
GONE.

42:53.237 --> 42:56.473
WE CAN ONLY WONDER IF THE
PRESENT STATE OF AMERICAN

42:56.540 --> 42:59.176
POLITICS IS CAPABLE OF PRODUCING
THEIR SUCCESSORS.

42:59.243 --> 43:01.745
I'M BILL WHITAKER.

